And this being ſo, where continued the Catholike Church? In France alone? And ſhall then the Part haue giuen a bill of diuorce to the whole? Shall then that which an ancient Father cried out be accompliſhed: I ſee that, which cannot be done;
Author li. contra Fulgent. inter ep. Aug. tom. 7. The Part of the Donatists hath ouercome the whole body; A corner of Afrike, hath excluded and thruſt out the whole world? What then ſhall become of the inheritance, to whome God the Father ſaid: Aske of me, and I will giue thee the Gentils for thine inheritance?
Pſal. 2. what then ſhall become of the title of Catholike, by which S. Aug. cont. ep. Fundament. Auguſtine profeſſeth himſelf to haue beene moſt of all held and kept in the Church?
